               <p>CHARLES ORTON. I am an apprentice to Mr. Thomas Dugard, who is a <rs id="t18181028-60-viclabel350" type="occupation">jeweller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-60-victim456 t18181028-60-viclabel350"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18181028-60-crimeloc351">Red Lion-street, Clerkenwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18181028-60-crimeloc351" type="placeName" value="Red Lion-street, Clerkenwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18181028-60-crimeloc351" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-60-off348 t18181028-60-crimeloc351"></join>; the prisoner was my master's <rs id="t18181028-60-deflabel352" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-60-defend455 t18181028-60-deflabel352"></join>. On the 8th of September I gave the work people some gold solder to work on, having first scratched on it, "coloured gold solder." I gave the prisoner some of it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ANDREWS, The other men might have had some with those words on it, as well as the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181810280024"></xptr>THOMAS DUGARD. In consequence of a discovery which was made, I told the prisoner that property was missing-he was taken to the watch-house. I saw him next day there, and he begged for mercy; I said I could say nothing to it, as I was afraid the robbery had been carried on to a great length. He said he should never have done it if he had not been persuaded by another person, whose name he said was Horn. We got a warrant, searched Horn's house, and found the property stated in the indictment, there.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>(See No. 1436.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18181028-60-verdict353" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18181028-60-verdict353" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Second Middlesex Jury, before Mr. Recorder.</p>
